23/04/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The government on Thursday (22 April) started the fourth round of talks on signing a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU.
The talks will focus on measures against organised crime, corruption and money laundering, as well as on transparency in utilising budget funds.
The sides are also to discuss the visa regime and the free movement of people.
In other news, parliament on Thursday postponed its decision on a bill compensating victims of political persecution.
Protestors representing the group tried to push their way inside the building but were stopped by police.
(Albanian Daily News - 23/04/04;
ATA - 22/04/04)
